Detailed Description

The S3ListPartsResult contains all the information about the listParts method.

Property Documentation

- (NSString *) bucket [read, write, retain]

The name of the bucket to which the multipart upload was initiated.

- (bool) isTruncated [read, write, assign]

Indicates whether the returned list of parts is truncated.

A value true indicates the list was truncated. A list may be truncated if the number of parts exceeds the limit specified by MaxParts.

- (NSString *) key [read, write, retain]

Tthe object key for which the multipart upload was initiated.

- (int) maxParts [read, write, assign]

The maxParts which was supplied in the request.

- (int) nextPartNumberMarker [read, write, assign]

When a list is truncated, specifies the last part that should be skipped over to resume listing.

Use this value for the partNumberMarker request property in a subsequent request.

- (int) partNumberMarker [read, write, assign]

The part number after which listing begins.

- (NSString *) storageClass [read, write, retain]

The class of storage used to store the uploaded object.

The upload ID identifying the multipart upload whose parts are being listed.
